And as soon as it left the
room, the computers worked,

00:48:44.810 --> 00:48:47.550 align:middle line:84%
the boards worked, and
everything was fine.

00:48:47.550 --> 00:48:49.590 align:middle line:84%
After the program
I told him, I said,

00:48:49.590 --> 00:48:51.390 align:middle line:90%
Howard, get rid of this thing.

00:48:51.390 --> 00:48:53.250 align:middle line:90%
I don't want it around.

00:48:53.250 --> 00:48:55.790 align:middle line:84%
He gave it to one
of our news guys.

00:48:55.790 --> 00:48:56.900 align:middle line:90%
His name was Darryl.

00:48:56.900 --> 00:48:58.390 align:middle line:90%
He gave it to him as a present.

00:48:58.390 --> 00:49:01.430 align:middle line:84%
Darryl was all excited
to get the Ouija board.

00:49:01.430 --> 00:49:05.970 align:middle line:84%
Two weeks later, Darryl was
fired, lost his job, lost

00:49:05.970 --> 00:49:07.790 align:middle line:90%
his relationship.

00:49:07.790 --> 00:49:09.950 align:middle line:84%
And we're convinced
to this day it

00:49:09.950 --> 00:49:11.550 align:middle line:90%
was because of the Ouija board.

00:49:11.550 --> 00:49:15.560 align:middle line:84%
So Rosemary, why do
you carry this around?

00:49:15.560 --> 00:49:16.710 align:middle line:90%
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

00:49:16.710 --> 00:49:20.340 align:middle line:84%
>> GUILEY: Well, I would like
to say that I was stopped by TSA

00:49:20.340 --> 00:49:23.547 align:middle line:84%
on the plane going through
security to get on the plane.

00:49:23.547 --> 00:49:24.630 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Because of this?

00:49:24.630 --> 00:49:27.700 align:middle line:84%
>> GUILEY: Well, I wasn't going
to put in unlocked baggage

00:49:27.700 --> 00:49:30.210 align:middle line:84%
either of my toys, so
I had them in carry-on.

00:49:30.210 --> 00:49:32.695 align:middle line:84%
And they went through the
x-ray machine a couple times,

00:49:32.695 --> 00:49:34.445 align:middle line:84%
and the the guy takes
it off, and he says,

00:49:34.445 --> 00:49:35.840 align:middle line:90%
what's in this bag?

00:49:35.840 --> 00:49:38.302 align:middle line:84%
I said, a Ouija board
and a ghost hunting box.

00:49:38.302 --> 00:49:40.460 align:middle line:90%
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

00:49:40.460 --> 00:49:43.700 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: I don't know how they
would let you on a plane with

00:49:43.700 --> 00:49:44.200 align:middle line:90%
this thing.

00:49:44.200 --> 00:49:46.670 align:middle line:84%
>> GUILEY: It does look like
it's going to blow something

00:49:46.670 --> 00:49:47.169 align:middle line:90%
up.

00:49:47.169 --> 00:49:49.280 align:middle line:84%
But they tested
it for explosives,

00:49:49.280 --> 00:49:52.310 align:middle line:84%
and I thought they were
going to take it apart.

00:49:52.310 --> 00:49:55.490 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, well, the
Ouija board, it's

00:49:55.490 --> 00:49:59.050 align:middle line:84%
probably the most infamous
device in the paranormal

00:49:59.050 --> 00:50:03.070 align:middle line:84%
because of the reputation it's
acquired, largely unfairly,

00:50:03.070 --> 00:50:03.604 align:middle line:90%
I might add.

00:50:03.604 --> 00:50:04.395 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Oh, sure.

00:50:04.395 --> 00:50:05.890 align:middle line:90%
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

00:50:05.890 --> 00:50:07.070 align:middle line:90%
>> GUILEY: It's a tool.

00:50:07.070 --> 00:50:08.060 align:middle line:90%
It's a tool.

00:50:08.060 --> 00:50:09.990 align:middle line:90%
And as a tool, it's neutral.

00:50:09.990 --> 00:50:13.040 align:middle line:84%
But it does have a
very checkered history.

00:50:13.040 --> 00:50:17.030 align:middle line:84%
As an investigation device, as
a spirit communication device,

00:50:17.030 --> 00:50:19.780 align:middle line:84%
it's not very practical,
because it's slow.

00:50:19.780 --> 00:50:22.960 align:middle line:84%
It spells out answers to
questions letter by letter.

00:50:22.960 --> 00:50:27.050 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes you just get
gibberish or nothing at all.

00:50:27.050 --> 00:50:31.090 align:middle line:84%
The ghost box is far more
efficient in that regard.

00:50:31.090 --> 00:50:34.020 align:middle line:84%
But many people are
fascinated by the Ouija board.

00:50:34.020 --> 00:50:37.340 align:middle line:84%
It's been around for a
little over 100 years now,

00:50:37.340 --> 00:50:39.541 align:middle line:84%
and it has an
incredible history--

00:50:39.541 --> 00:50:41.290 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Who in the
heck would invent it?

00:50:41.290 --> 00:50:42.248 align:middle line:90%
>> GUILEY: --of mayhem.

00:50:42.248 --> 00:50:44.020 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Who would
invent this thing?

00:50:44.020 --> 00:50:48.290 align:middle line:84%
>> GUILEY: Actually, it evolved
out of a number of spirit

00:50:48.290 --> 00:50:50.190 align:middle line:90%
communication devices.

00:50:50.190 --> 00:50:53.640 align:middle line:84%
This little pointer
here on the board,

00:50:53.640 --> 00:50:55.930 align:middle line:84%
which is called the
planchette, actually

00:50:55.930 --> 00:50:58.510 align:middle line:84%
had a precursor in
spiritualism days

00:50:58.510 --> 00:51:00.910 align:middle line:84%
with a device called
the planchette, which

00:51:00.910 --> 00:51:03.210 align:middle line:84%
was shaped very
similarly, and it

00:51:03.210 --> 00:51:05.900 align:middle line:90%
had three very long legs on it.

00:51:05.900 --> 00:51:07.990 align:middle line:90%
This was a pencil.

00:51:07.990 --> 00:51:10.660 align:middle line:84%
And that you put your
hands on the device

00:51:10.660 --> 00:51:13.230 align:middle line:84%
on a blank piece of
paper and asked spirits

00:51:13.230 --> 00:51:16.340 align:middle line:84%
to answer questions, and
hopefully your movements

00:51:16.340 --> 00:51:18.650 align:middle line:84%
would literally
write out an answer.

00:51:18.650 --> 00:51:21.530 align:middle line:84%
Well, this is modified
now on the Ouija board.

00:51:21.530 --> 00:51:25.520 align:middle line:84%
We've had many pointing
devices throughout history

00:51:25.520 --> 00:51:29.270 align:middle line:84%
where we have asked the gods
to divine the future for us

00:51:29.270 --> 00:51:31.250 align:middle line:90%
by pointing to things.

00:51:31.250 --> 00:51:34.480 align:middle line:84%
And so the Ouija board
actually evolved out of that.

00:51:34.480 --> 00:51:38.360 align:middle line:84%
Some very smart businessmen
in the late 1800s

00:51:38.360 --> 00:51:41.300 align:middle line:84%
read about these pointing
devices that were literally

00:51:41.300 --> 00:51:44.230 align:middle line:84%
taking the country by
storm, especially in Ohio.

00:51:44.230 --> 00:51:49.230 align:middle line:84%
Ohio was a hotbed of
spiritualism in the 1800s.

00:51:49.230 --> 00:51:53.110 align:middle line:84%
And newspaper articles about
the pointing devices they used

00:51:53.110 --> 00:51:56.769 align:middle line:84%
caught the attention of some
toy manufacturers in Baltimore.

00:51:56.769 --> 00:51:57.310 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: OK.

00:51:57.310 --> 00:51:59.175 align:middle line:84%
>> GUILEY: And they
saw a brilliant idea.

00:51:59.175 --> 00:52:00.591 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: And they
made a fortune.

00:52:00.591 --> 00:52:03.920 align:middle line:84%
>> GUILEY: Made a fortune,
but not without a very strange

00:52:03.920 --> 00:52:05.540 align:middle line:90%
and tumultuous history.

00:52:05.540 --> 00:52:09.585 align:middle line:84%
Internally in the company,
there was lots of conflict.

00:52:09.585 --> 00:52:10.460 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Infighting?

00:52:10.460 --> 00:52:11.530 align:middle line:90%
>> GUILEY: Infighting.

00:52:11.530 --> 00:52:15.240 align:middle line:84%
The original patent holders
got out of the business.

00:52:15.240 --> 00:52:18.050 align:middle line:84%
A man who was a
painter and a varnisher

00:52:18.050 --> 00:52:20.300 align:middle line:84%
by trade-- and his name
is on the board today,

00:52:20.300 --> 00:52:25.140 align:middle line:84%
William Fuld-- took
over the toy company

00:52:25.140 --> 00:52:30.365 align:middle line:84%
and literally turned the Ouija
board into a global media hit.

00:52:30.365 --> 00:52:32.990 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: I got to tell you, if
I was on a plane with you and I

00:52:32.990 --> 00:52:36.140 align:middle line:84%
had heard that you had brought
a Ouija board on that plane,

00:52:36.140 --> 00:52:37.650 align:middle line:90%
I would have gotten off.

00:52:37.650 --> 00:52:39.935 align:middle line:84%
I would have taken
a different flight.

00:52:39.935 --> 00:52:41.171 align:middle line:90%
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

00:52:41.171 --> 00:52:41.670 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:52:41.670 --> 00:52:44.620 align:middle line:84%
Let's grab a volunteer
from our audience.

00:52:44.620 --> 00:52:46.760 align:middle line:84%
Anybody out there that
wants to take a chance?

00:52:46.760 --> 00:52:47.930 align:middle line:90%
Yes, come on up.

00:52:47.930 --> 00:52:48.760 align:middle line:90%
What's your name?

00:52:48.760 --> 00:52:49.320 align:middle line:90%
>> AUDIENCE: Juan.

00:52:49.320 --> 00:52:50.590 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Juan, come on over.

00:52:50.590 --> 00:52:52.160 align:middle line:90%
Have a seat here.

00:52:52.160 --> 00:52:56.170 align:middle line:84%
And Rosemary, why don't we
just-- it may or may not work--

00:52:56.170 --> 00:52:57.000 align:middle line:90%
have a seat, Juan--

00:52:57.000 --> 00:52:57.958 align:middle line:90%
>> AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:52:57.958 --> 00:53:01.404 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: --but explain what
you and Juan have to do here.

00:53:01.404 --> 00:53:03.820 align:middle line:84%
>> GUILEY: The board is best
worked by two or more people.

00:53:03.820 --> 00:53:04.897 align:middle line:90%
Two is really ideal.

00:53:04.897 --> 00:53:06.730 align:middle line:84%
You can have as many
as four, but you've all

00:53:06.730 --> 00:53:09.210 align:middle line:84%
got to put your fingers
on the planchette.

00:53:09.210 --> 00:53:14.760 align:middle line:84%
One person can work a board too,
but two blending their energy--

00:53:14.760 --> 00:53:17.240 align:middle line:84%
Juan, what you and I
will do is concentrate

00:53:17.240 --> 00:53:19.410 align:middle line:84%
on communicating with
the spirit world.

00:53:19.410 --> 00:53:21.120 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes a door
opens right away,

00:53:21.120 --> 00:53:25.550 align:middle line:84%
and the pointer
begins moving around

00:53:25.550 --> 00:53:31.227 align:middle line:84%
and stops on various
letters, and you

00:53:31.227 --> 00:53:32.560 align:middle line:90%
might get something spelled out.

00:53:32.560 --> 00:53:34.440 align:middle line:84%
A lot of times you
just get gibberish.

00:53:34.440 --> 00:53:37.300 align:middle line:84%
But the idea is to put
your fingers very lightly

00:53:37.300 --> 00:53:39.940 align:middle line:90%
on the planchette.

00:53:39.940 --> 00:53:42.370 align:middle line:84%
Critics have said, oh,
people move this around.

00:53:42.370 --> 00:53:43.970 align:middle line:84%
Well, I have worked
the Ouija board

00:53:43.970 --> 00:53:45.739 align:middle line:84%
at times where the
pointer is literally

00:53:45.739 --> 00:53:46.780 align:middle line:90%
sailing around the board.

00:53:46.780 --> 00:53:48.440 align:middle line:84%
You can hardly keep
your fingers on it.

00:53:48.440 --> 00:53:50.870 align:middle line:90%
So what is moving this pointer?

00:53:50.870 --> 00:53:52.636 align:middle line:90%
Well, it may be a spirit.

00:53:52.636 --> 00:53:54.010 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Well,
let's try it out.

00:53:54.010 --> 00:53:54.070 align:middle line:90%
>> GUILEY: Let's give it a shot.

00:53:54.070 --> 00:53:55.590 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: But
before we go, Juan,

00:53:55.590 --> 00:53:59.470 align:middle line:84%
raise your right hand and
promise not to be upset with me

00:53:59.470 --> 00:54:02.548 align:middle line:84%
if anything should happen to
you because of the Ouija board.

00:54:02.548 --> 00:54:04.250 align:middle line:84%
>> AUDIENCE: I promise not to
be upset with you if anything

00:54:04.250 --> 00:54:05.598 align:middle line:84%
should happen because
of the Ouija board.

00:54:05.598 --> 00:54:06.434 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Thank you, Juan.

00:54:06.434 --> 00:54:06.852 align:middle line:90%
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

00:54:06.852 --> 00:54:07.930 align:middle line:90%
Now take it away.

00:54:07.930 --> 00:54:10.020 align:middle line:84%
That's my little
disclaimer for the moment.

00:54:10.020 --> 00:54:12.061 align:middle line:84%
>> GUILEY: Now I've used
these since I was a kid.

00:54:12.061 --> 00:54:15.800 align:middle line:84%
Not a whole lot, because I find
other things more effective.

00:54:15.800 --> 00:54:17.910 align:middle line:84%
And I've been cursed
out by spirits,

00:54:17.910 --> 00:54:19.710 align:middle line:84%
and I've gotten
a nasty messages,

00:54:19.710 --> 00:54:22.070 align:middle line:84%
but I've never
felt that anything

00:54:22.070 --> 00:54:24.030 align:middle line:90%
has followed me around.

00:54:24.030 --> 00:54:24.530 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:54:24.530 --> 00:54:30.260 align:middle line:84%
So Juan, I'm going to put the
planchette kind of like this

00:54:30.260 --> 00:54:31.670 align:middle line:90%
so we can get it pointing.

00:54:31.670 --> 00:54:32.390 align:middle line:90%
>> AUDIENCE: OK.

00:54:32.390 --> 00:54:33.870 align:middle line:84%
>> GUILEY: Or could
we turn the board?

00:54:33.870 --> 00:54:34.200 align:middle line:90%
Would that be--

00:54:34.200 --> 00:54:34.330 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Yeah, absolutely.

00:54:34.330 --> 00:54:35.160 align:middle line:90%
>> GUILEY: --all right?

00:54:35.160 --> 00:54:35.540 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Yeah.

00:54:35.540 --> 00:54:37.290 align:middle line:84%
>> GUILEY: Let's turn
the board like this.

00:54:37.290 --> 00:54:43.020 align:middle line:84%
And put your fingers
lightly on the planchette,

00:54:43.020 --> 00:54:44.900 align:middle line:90%
and just concentrate.

00:54:44.900 --> 00:54:46.840 align:middle line:84%
It's a good idea
to ask questions.

00:54:46.840 --> 00:54:48.590 align:middle line:84%
Now the Ouija board
will spell things out.

00:54:48.590 --> 00:54:51.780 align:middle line:84%
It's got numbers,
yes, no, goodbye,

00:54:51.780 --> 00:54:53.940 align:middle line:84%
and sometimes
it'll point to yes.

00:54:53.940 --> 00:54:56.685 align:middle line:84%
It's often a good idea to
ask yes or no questions.

00:54:56.685 --> 00:54:58.750 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: It's already moving.

00:54:58.750 --> 00:55:00.850 align:middle line:84%
And neither one of
you is pushing it.

00:55:00.850 --> 00:55:05.360 align:middle line:84%
>> GUILEY: So what I did was
I asked for something to start

00:55:05.360 --> 00:55:08.850 align:middle line:84%
communicating, and
it's pointing to yes.

00:55:08.850 --> 00:55:12.910 align:middle line:84%
Yes, something is here who
wishes to make itself known.

00:55:12.910 --> 00:55:16.205 align:middle line:84%
And can you spell your
name out for us, please?

00:55:16.205 --> 00:55:18.740 align:middle line:90%


00:55:18.740 --> 00:55:23.490 align:middle line:84%
Now I've always used the
clear window in the pointer

00:55:23.490 --> 00:55:25.350 align:middle line:84%
as the indication
for the letter.

00:55:25.350 --> 00:55:31.550 align:middle line:84%
So it stopped on O. Spell
your name out, please.

00:55:31.550 --> 00:55:35.040 align:middle line:90%
O-B. Obi-Wan Kenobi.

00:55:35.040 --> 00:55:37.530 align:middle line:90%
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

00:55:37.530 --> 00:55:42.040 align:middle line:84%
And we'll see if we
get any-- sometimes

00:55:42.040 --> 00:55:43.670 align:middle line:84%
the planchette
will wander around,

00:55:43.670 --> 00:55:44.900 align:middle line:90%
and you have to tell them.

00:55:44.900 --> 00:55:48.140 align:middle line:84%
You have to discipline them and
say, look, speed it up a bit.

00:55:48.140 --> 00:56:03.320 align:middle line:84%
Give us something--
O-B-O. O-B-O 1.

00:56:03.320 --> 00:56:05.811 align:middle line:84%
Now to me that's not making
a whole lot of sense.

00:56:05.811 --> 00:56:07.060 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: It's Obi-One Kenobi.

00:56:07.060 --> 00:56:08.620 align:middle line:90%
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

00:56:08.620 --> 00:56:10.740 align:middle line:84%
>> GUILEY: And we just
fell off the board there,

00:56:10.740 --> 00:56:14.180 align:middle line:84%
so I have to give
the planchette--

00:56:14.180 --> 00:56:17.930 align:middle line:84%
sometimes when you have this on
a big table and you get a lot

00:56:17.930 --> 00:56:21.520 align:middle line:84%
of spirit activity, it will
fly off the board and sometimes

00:56:21.520 --> 00:56:23.280 align:middle line:90%
even off the table.

00:56:23.280 --> 00:56:23.970 align:middle line:90%
So spirit--

00:56:23.970 --> 00:56:27.060 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: What if the spirit's
from a different planet and his

00:56:27.060 --> 00:56:30.240 align:middle line:90%
name was Obo 1?

00:56:30.240 --> 00:56:31.820 align:middle line:90%
>> GUILEY: Anything's possible.

00:56:31.820 --> 00:56:35.790 align:middle line:84%
When you're dealing with
non-human communicators

00:56:35.790 --> 00:56:38.240 align:middle line:84%
in many cases, what
makes sense to them

00:56:38.240 --> 00:56:41.090 align:middle line:84%
is not going to
make sense to us.

00:56:41.090 --> 00:56:44.310 align:middle line:90%
So let me ask a question here.

00:56:44.310 --> 00:56:44.999 align:middle line:90%
Obo 1--

00:56:44.999 --> 00:56:45.665 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Obo 1.

00:56:45.665 --> 00:56:46.331 align:middle line:90%
That's his name.

00:56:46.331 --> 00:56:48.060 align:middle line:84%
>> GUILEY: Obo 1,
is that your name?

00:56:48.060 --> 00:56:48.870 align:middle line:90%
Yes or no?

00:56:48.870 --> 00:56:51.780 align:middle line:90%


00:56:51.780 --> 00:56:53.977 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: It's pointing
to the yes right there.

00:56:53.977 --> 00:56:54.560 align:middle line:90%
>> GUILEY: OK.

00:56:54.560 --> 00:56:55.143 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: See?

00:56:55.143 --> 00:56:55.725 align:middle line:90%
I told you.

00:56:55.725 --> 00:56:58.625 align:middle line:90%
He's from another place.

00:56:58.625 --> 00:57:00.125 align:middle line:84%
>> GUILEY: Are you
a helpful spirit?

00:57:00.125 --> 00:57:03.269 align:middle line:90%


00:57:03.269 --> 00:57:04.560 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Can I ask a question?

00:57:04.560 --> 00:57:07.220 align:middle line:90%
>> GUILEY: Oh, absolutely.

00:57:07.220 --> 00:57:08.340 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Obo?

00:57:08.340 --> 00:57:10.430 align:middle line:90%
Do you watch "Beyond Belief"?

00:57:10.430 --> 00:57:16.050 align:middle line:90%
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

00:57:16.050 --> 00:57:18.327 align:middle line:84%
He said yes, so they're
picking it up somewhere.

00:57:18.327 --> 00:57:20.160 align:middle line:84%
>> GUILEY: One of your
biggest fans, George,

00:57:20.160 --> 00:57:21.190 align:middle line:90%
and you didn't know it.

00:57:21.190 --> 00:57:22.590 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Probably is.

00:57:22.590 --> 00:57:24.421 align:middle line:90%
So they are interested in media.

00:57:24.421 --> 00:57:26.920 align:middle line:84%
>> GUILEY: There's an audience
in another dimension watching

00:57:26.920 --> 00:57:27.780 align:middle line:90%
this show.

00:57:27.780 --> 00:57:32.060 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Obo, are
you good or evil?

00:57:32.060 --> 00:57:37.610 align:middle line:90%


00:57:37.610 --> 00:57:39.490 align:middle line:90%
Good or evil?

00:57:39.490 --> 00:57:42.340 align:middle line:84%
>> GUILEY: So we'll probably
have to spell out something.

00:57:42.340 --> 00:57:44.520 align:middle line:90%
Good or evil?

